(2)
x = \frac12 (4 \pm \sqrt{16 + 40}) \;=\; \frac12(4 \pm \sqrt{56})\; = \;\frac12 (4 \pm \sqrt{4\cdot 14}) \;=\; \frac12 (4 \pm \sqrt{4}\sqrt{14})\;
 = \;\frac12 (4 \pm 2\sqrt{14})\;=\; \frac 12 \cdot 4 \pm \frac12 \cdot 2\sqrt{14}\;\; = \;\;2 \pm \sqrt{14}
